					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1017679#post-2107537</guid>
				<title>God damn you, Slappy</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1017679/scp-2650#post-2107537</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2014 12:30:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>A Random Day</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1841781</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>As a child, only two things scared me: Slappy from Goosebumps and my father's threats to sell me to the orphanage. He knew how to inspire discipline.</p> <p>Thanks to Zolgamax and MorgiePie in chat for looking over this.</p> <p>See more of my work on my <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/dr-arvind-desais-personnel-file">author page</a>!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1017679#post-2107529</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1017679/scp-2650#post-2107529</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 11 Sep 2014 12:08:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>VAElynx</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>914331</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ultimately, I like this - there are a couple things that bug me though.</p> <blockquote> <p>that plays only FPA Preadolescent Programming.</p> </blockquote> <p>I don't really like the shortcut and the capitalization. Saying &quot;recorded broadcasts and programming fit for preadolescent viewing&quot; would fit better.<br /> Also, do SCP-2650-1 age normally or not?</p> <blockquote> <p>SCP-2650-B should be fed once per day with five (5) Standard D-Class Capsule Rations using the Rations Transference Device.</p> </blockquote> <p>Meh. If I understand correctly what you mean, it's a little far too future-tech for me with respect to the Foundation.</p> <blockquote> <p>Deterrence Device activation rates have been reduced by 300%.</p> </blockquote> <p><strong>NO</strong><br /> This makes zero fucking sense. Reduction by 100% means that you don't have to use them anymore, after all.</p> <p>EDIT: And now I can upvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
